The vibrational peak at 1390 cm−1 which is only observed in sample HCD2 is typically associated with C-H bending vibrations which is related to methyl (–CH



                                 3


                        ) or methylene (–CH



                                 2


                        ) groups. This peak can also indicate the presence of aromatic compounds or other hydrocarbons that exhibit similar bending vibrations [30].
